(Lakemont Green Roof and Stormwater Program) Tj
T*
(Source ID: lakemont_green_roofs) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This fictional city brief was created for teaching RAG retrieval and evaluation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Lakemont is a fictional lakeside city where short storms cause street flooding and send) Tj
T*
(polluted runoff into Lake Aster. The green roof and stormwater program focuses on the) Tj
T*
(Hillcrest, West Dock, and Museum Quarter neighborhoods. These areas have many flat roofs,) Tj
T*
(parking lots, and old combined sewers.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The main target is to capture the first 25 millimeters of rainfall during common storms. City) Tj
T*
(engineers call this the first-flush problem because the first part of a storm often carries) Tj
T*
(oil, dust, and litter from streets into the lake. Capturing that water improves lake quality) Tj
T*
(and reduces sewer overflow.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Lakemont offers grants for green roofs on apartment buildings, schools, and public offices. A) Tj
T*
(green roof must include a waterproof layer, soil medium, drought-tolerant plants, and safe) Tj
T*
(maintenance access. The city does not require every building to participate, but larger) Tj
T*
(renovations must submit a stormwater retention plan.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Permeable pavement is planned for West Dock parking lanes and two public squares near the) Tj
T*
(museum. Unlike normal asphalt, permeable pavement lets rain pass through gaps into a stone) Tj
T*
(layer below. The program pairs permeable pavement with rain gardens so water has more than one) Tj
T*
(place to slow down.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Schools receive cisterns that collect roof water for gardens and cleaning outdoor equipment.) Tj
T*
(The education department will use the cisterns as climate lessons, but the infrastructure goal) Tj
T*
(is practical: reduce pressure on sewers during fast storms. The program expects the school) Tj
T*
(cisterns to be small but visible examples.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The city makes a clear distinction between stormwater adaptation and emergency flood response.) Tj
T*
(Green roofs, rain gardens, and permeable pavement reduce runoff before streets flood. Sandbags) Tj
T*
(and temporary road closures are response tools after flooding has already started. Lakemont) Tj
T*
(wants more investment before the emergency phase.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The budget is 4.2 million city credits for the first two years, including 1.5 million for) Tj
T*
(private building grants. Success is measured by retained stormwater volume, fewer sewer) Tj
T*
(overflow warnings, and lower bacteria counts near the West Dock swimming area. The plan warns) Tj
T*
(that maintenance is essential because clogged pavement stops absorbing water.) Tj
T*
() Tj
